-Antimalarial agent that kills sensitive malaria parasites
 -Take the medicine once a week after your main meal (NOT ON AN EMPTY STOMACH)
 -Start using 1 week before entering the area
 -Continue using through out the stay,and at least 4 weeks after leave
 -Take missed doses as soon as possible, but skip them if it is almost time for next dose
 -Consult your doctor if you have allergies, mental illnesses, seizures, or are taking similar medicines
 -Some side effects of drug: stomach pain, headache, muscle ache, tiredness, vomiting
 -Visit http://www.drugs.com/cdi/mefloquine.html for more information

-Tetracycline antibiotic that helps to fight bacteria in the body
 -Take the medicine everyday at the same time with food
 -Start using 1-2 days before entering the area
 -Continue using through out the stay,and at least 28 days after leave
 -Take missed doses as soon as possible, but skip them if it is almost time for next dose
 -Consult your doctor if you have liver or kidney disease, or are taking supplements and other medicines
 -Some side effects of drug: stomach pain, headache, diarrhea, fever, weakness
 -Visit http://www.drugs.com/doxycycline.html for more information
Have you taken your drug today ?

-Interferes with growth of parasites in red blood cells
 -Take the medicine everyday at the same time with food
 -Start using 1-2 days before entering the area
 -Continue using through out the stay,and at least 7 days after leave
 -Take missed doses as soon as possible, but skip them if it is almost time for next dose
 -Consult your doctor if you have liver or kidney disease, or malaria complications
 -Some side effects of drug: stomach pain, headache, diarrhea, fever, weakness
 -Visit http://www.drugs.com/malarone.html for more information
